 {"id":"bd-mblr.3.4.1","title":"No-mock critical-path CI gate rule","description":"Enforce CI rule that critical-path verification must be satisfied by real-backend tests, not mock-only suites. Output: auditable rule implementation and failure messaging.","design":"Implement rule over structured invariant/test mapping generated from bd-mblr.1.3.2 artifacts.","acceptance_criteria":"- CI rule evaluates non-mock critical-path evidence with deterministic pass/fail semantics.
